message.content:
cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with real-time facial segmentation and performance capture using deep learning techniques. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of facial segmentation for compositing partial 3D face models on input images for facial manipulation tasks. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with real-time processing of multimedia data (RGB images) for facial performance capture. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of facial performance capture for virtual make-up and face replacement, which are relevant to HCI applications. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category as the paper uses deep learning techniques for facial segmentation and performance capture.
